The paper focuses on weakly-supervised temporal action localization, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel framework that involves adversarial learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework involves sequence growing and feature mining, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves classification and localization, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
